.TH HSH 1 "January 2026" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter that reads commands from standard input and executes them.
.PP
The shell searches for executables in the directories listed in the PATH environment variable. Full paths and relative paths are also supported.
.SH INVOCATION
.B Interactive mode:
Run
.B ./hsh
and type commands at the prompt.
.PP
.B Non-interactive mode:
Pipe commands to the shell, e.g.
.B echo "ls" | ./hsh
.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ ./hsh
$ ls
AUTHORS  hsh  main.c  README.md  shell.h
$ pwd
/home/user/simple_shell
$ /bin/ls -la
total 48
drwxr-xr-x 2 user user 4096 Jan 9 12:00 .
$ echo hello
hello
$ exit
.fi
.PP
Non-interactive:
.nf
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh
$ echo "pwd" | ./hsh
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success. Returns 127 if a command is not found.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
Colon-separated list of directories to search for commands.
.SH AUTHORS
Alexander Durant <https://github.com/starfruitone>
.br
Nano420X <https://github.com/Nano420x>
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2)
